It is powered by 4.0-litre (3,994 cc) V12 engine developed by Cosworth. The naturally aspirated V12 engine produces 488kW and boasts one of the highest power-to-weight ratios. It weighs in at 986 kg and the engine can run at an amazing maximum of 12 000rpm. Watch this exclusive video of the T.50’s engine running at full speed on a lap simulation of Le Mans reaching its ultimate 12 100rpm – the highest-revving road-going V12 in history – https://youtu.be/9PuFRto323w  It is said that only 100 of these T-50s will be manufactured with the first delivery in 2022. Source: Aileen Lekschat – Influenceassociates.com